ads.author: Glenn Musto
ads.title: Atari Tempest Arcade Machine – 1981 Classic Reproduction, w/ modern electronics
ads.description: Modern Re-Creation of the Legendary 1981 Atari Tempest Step back into the golden age of arcades—without the headaches of vintage hardware. This is a brand-new machine built in the style of the iconic Atari Tempest, faithfully recreating the sights, sounds, and gameplay of the original classic. Authentic Gameplay As a Tempest champion in the 1980s and owner of an original machine, I can personally vouch that the gameplay here is spot-on, indistinguishable from a brand-new Tempest as it played in arcades back in the day. Why This Machine Is Better The truth is, the original Tempest was a maintenance nightmare. Its color X-Y CRT monitor burned itself out, circuit boards constantly failed, and many machines ended up in the dump. That’s why working originals are nearly impossible to find—and even if you do, you’re stuck battling those same issues. This machine eliminates every one of those problems, while giving you more: 24" LCD with LED backlighting (IPS panel, any-angle viewing — no fragile CRT). New spinner with dual sealed bearings for silky-smooth precision control. 50-watt stereo sound system with subwoofer, volume control pod, and headphone jack (not just old mono sound). Commercial-grade power: 500+ watt ATX supply plus built-in 1,000-joule surge protector with EMI/RFI filtering. Universal JAMMA harness for plug-and-play swap of other JAMMA boards. Durable build: 3⁄4” commercial-grade cabinet, stainless steel control panel hardware, polycarbonate overlay and graphics (not scratch-prone vinyl). LED marquee lighting (no hot fluorescent bulbs). Poly wheels that roll without scratching floors. Freeplay setup for home use (no quarters required). Choice of keyed vault-style lock or thumb lock for the front door. Extra Features Tempest & Tempest Tubes — play classic levels and unlock options never before accessible. Levels 1 through 99 — explore stages you may have never reached in the arcade. Demonstration Mode: blast through tubes, clear spikes, or jump levels instantly—perfect for testing all 99 levels, whether you’re a pro or a newcomer. Why It Matters This is not just another retro cabinet with emulation slapped inside. It’s a commercial-grade, modernized Tempest machine built to last a lifetime, with gameplay so accurate that arcade veterans can’t tell the difference. Full instructions come with order, including game options, settings, default settings, etc. Defaults are: Game difficulty is Medium, Bonus Life awarded at 20,000 points, and 3 lives per game. Local pickup or buyer arranged packing and shipping. Game is located in Saint Petersburg Florida. If you want it shipped, I will make it available any time at my home for your freight company to pick it up. You must make all arrangements. Size at control panel - approx. 25" wide x 33" deep. Heigth - approx. 73" cabinet top to floor with wheels. Weight - approx. only 170 lbs. (thanks to the LCD/LED monitor). Palleted shipping weight - approx. 210 lbs.

The player is rated by the amount of pressure he can applied and withstand from the machine, of like all arm wrestling machine the object is the force the lever all the way to the opposing side. ads.title: Police Trainer, Upright Arcade, P&P Marketing 1996
ads.description: Vintage Upright Arcade – Police Trainer (P&P Marketing, 1996) Price: $475 (Negotiable, but not by much) Test your reflexes and accuracy with this original Police Trainer upright arcade cabinet from 1996. Developed by P&P Marketing, Police Trainer is a fast-paced shooter that puts players through a series of training exercises — from target practice to reaction drills — making it one of the most unique skill-based arcade shooters of the 90s. Condition: - Cabinet is original but needs some love due to age. - Monitor powers on, image is good, but likely needs new caps for long-term reliability. - Lights and sound both work. - Controls function, but the guns need recalibration. - Sold as-is. Highlights: - Classic 90s shooter with training-style gameplay. - Upright cabinet design with dual light guns. - Fully playable — monitor, lights, and sound all working. - Great candidate for restoration or display in a retro collection. Important: - Price is $475, negotiable but only slightly. - Serious buyers only.

ads.author: Benjamin Cook
ads.title: 1996 Sega Wave Runner Arcade Machine
ads.description:
*If it's up, it's available.
Local pickup near Boiling Springs SC.
Electronic payments (Cash app, venmo, zelle etc) are not accepted. Cash only please*

I had planned on restoring this arcade machine but life got in the way. It powers on and works to an extent but it needs TLC to get it fully functional. The picture convergence needs help. The jet ski needs an air compressor to make the ride functional which is missing so I never could test it. There's also a piece of aluminum trim on the left side of the jet ski that was missing when I got it. The Sega Model 2 inside has been replaced so the old one is included.

You will need to bring a trailer with a ramp to load it. Both pieces are on wheels so it's relatively easy to move but very heavy.

ads.author: John Enamait
ads.title: Boppin’ Bugs Full-Size Arcade Game – WORKS – Set to Free Play
ads.description:
For sale is a full-size commercial arcade game: Boppin\u2019 Bugs. This is a genuine coin-op arcade cabinet\u2014not a toy, not a countertop game.

The game works properly and is currently set to free play. Lights, sounds, digital score display, and gameplay all function as they should. I have a video of the game operating and can send it to serious buyers.

Condition (please read):
This is a used arcade machine and it shows its age cosmetically. Expect scuffs, wear, and cosmetic imperfections consistent with a real arcade game that was played and enjoyed. Structurally solid and fully playable. Nothing is being hidden\u2014photos accurately reflect condition.

Details:
\u2022 Full-size commercial arcade cabinet
\u2022 Works and plays correctly
\u2022 Currently set to free play
\u2022 Coin door installed (50\u00a2 mech present)
\u2022 Key included for rear cabinet
\u2022 No key for front coin mechanism
\u2022 Solid wood construction
\u2022 Great for a game room, basement, garage, church, daycare, brewery, or rec space

Pickup / Logistics:
\u2022 Local pickup only
\u2022 Large and heavy cabinet\u2014bring appropriate help and vehicle
\u2022 I can assist with basic loading, but cannot deliver or ship

Other Notes:
\u2022 Sold as-is due to age (standard for arcade equipment)
\u2022 No trades
\u2022 If the listing is up, it\u2019s still available

This is a fun, eye-catching arcade piece that still works and is a blast to play. Priced fairly at $850.

ads.author: Allen Robinson
ads.title: Double Axle, Upright Arcade, Taitio 1990
ads.description: Vintage Upright Arcade – Double Axle (Taito, 1990) Price: $400, Negotiable (but not by much) Bring home a piece of arcade racing history! This is an original Double Axle upright cabinet from Taito (1990). Known for its rugged off-road truck racing gameplay, Double Axle puts players behind the wheel of massive monster trucks, battling through dirt tracks, jumps, and obstacles. It’s a rare find that captures the excitement of 90s arcade culture. Condition: - Cabinet is original and shows its age — it needs some love. - Monitor has been converted to LCD. - Lights power on. - Sound is present. - Game plays and works! Highlights: - Classic Taito racing arcade with unique monster truck gameplay. - LCD conversion makes it easier to maintain. - Great candidate for restoration or display in a collection. - A working cabinet from 1990 — not something you see every day. Important: - Price is negotiable, but only slightly. - Sold as-is. - Serious buyers only.

ads.author: Allen Robinson
ads.title: Pole Position, Upright Arcade, Atari/Namco 1982
ads.description:
Vintage Upright Arcade \u2013 Pole Position (Atari/Namco, November 1982)
Price:  $475, Negotiable (but not by much)
Step into racing history with this original Pole Position upright cabinet \u2014 one of the most iconic arcade racers ever made. Released in 1982 by Atari/Namco, Pole Position was a groundbreaking driving simulator that set the standard for racing games. It\u2019s widely recognized as one of the Top 50 most historically important video games of all time.
Condition:
- Cabinet is very old and needs some love.
- Boards need work and likely new caps.
- Monitor does not power on.
- Lights come on.
- No sound currently.
- This is a project cabinet \u2014 perfect for restoration enthusiasts or collectors.
Highlights:
- Classic upright racer with simulator-style gameplay.
- Rare piece of arcade history from the golden age.
- Great candidate for restoration or display in a collection.
Important:
- Price is negotiable, but only slightly.
- Sold as-is.
- Serious buyers only.

ads.author: Tom Grizzard
ads.title: 1978 Bally PLAYBOY pinball machine -New Playfield, new cabinet decals
ads.description:
Experience nostalgia with this classic 1978 Bally PLAYBOY pinball machine. This machine has been given a new lease of life with a brand new playfield and cabinet decals, making it the perfect addition to any arcade or pinball collection. The machine boasts the iconic PLAYBOY branding and provides endless hours of entertainment for all ages. Don't miss out on the chance to own this timeless piece of gaming history.

Notable Features:     Flippers (2), Pop bumpers (3), Slingshots (2), Standup targets (6), 5-bank drop targets (1), Star rollover (1), Upper left kickback lane (the Grotto).

The backglass depicts Hugh Hefner with 1976 Playmate Patti McGuire and 1977 Playmate Sondra Theodore. Tom Nieman, VP of Marketing for Bally Pinball, told us his name or initials appeared on most backglasses of this time period for which he obtained the license. On this game, his name appears on the champagne bottle.

The start-up tune, Grotto tune, and bonus score countdown tune resemble portions of Cy Coleman's "Playboy's Theme" from the 1969 TV show "Playboy After Dark". An article in the Spring 2019 issue of Playboy magazine about the "Singing Playmates" mentioned that their producer Vic Caesar "arranged the surprisingly famous theme to the Playboy pinball game."

Good condition. Everything works.

 
Will ship via freight carrier at buyer's expense... contact for quote.  Local delivery available for a nominal fee.

ads.description: Vintage Upright Arcade – Capcom Bowling (Capcom, 1988) Price: $275 (or best offer) Step back into the late 80s with this original Capcom Bowling upright arcade cabinet. Released in 1988, this sports title brought the fun of bowling into the arcade scene, complete with competitive play and retro charm. It’s a nostalgic piece for collectors and fans of Capcom’s unique arcade lineup. Condition: - Cabinet is very old and needs a lot of love. - Monitor does not currently power on — likely needs new caps. - Nothing comes on at the moment; best to start troubleshooting with the power supply and work your way from there. - Sold as-is. Highlights: - Classic Capcom sports arcade with bowling gameplay. - Upright cabinet design from the golden age of arcades. - Great candidate for restoration or display in a retro collection. Important: - Price is $275, or best offer - Serious buyers only.
